Great environment and lovely workers, u met the owner when I went in and learned lots of history about this brand. Definitely will come back when I'm visiting San Francisco

Love the Red Velvet cupcakes! Will definitely be back to try other stuff. Everything looks soo good I will be back. Wish the price can just be a bit cheaper. Yes I can't afford to come that often with these prices but will be back!

Soooooo goooood! A must try.

i wanted to give it a 5, but i cant because i never tried the drinks yet [: however for the macaron ice cream sandwich. This place makes me happy :D  If you are a coffee lover you have to try Coffee Toffee Crunch Shake! The red velvet cupcakes are so cute and just the right size to satisfy your cupcake craving!

When I inquired if they were open (as the sign indicates) she was talking on her phone and told me no. How weird! Bummer that I couldn't try their products and that the customer service wasn't better.
This place is great! They have amazing non dairy choices and the flavors are yummy!

From far the best ice cream in San Francisco and a great concept, they actually use amazing home made macarons to make ice cream sandwiches ! They also do regular ice cream, cookies, cakes, coffee, etc.. A must in the city !

Products aren’t bad, but the lady who works in the afternoon shift, needs a lot training and how to deal Custmors, I had a bad  experience with her, made me and my family not to come any more. A worker with short temper shouldn’t be  behind the counter at all.

Came here on a Sunday afternoon, it wasn't too crowded. Amazing macaron ice cream sandwich, was my first time and i absolutely loved it. Just like grandma used to make! The original is your classic rice pudding but if you’re feeling adventurous they have some other equally delicious flavors.  The beat part about loving Cup is the rewards program: buy 10 get one free! I come every chance my diet allows 😊
Nice

Quick, delicious fro yo.

Vegan frozen yogurt is terrible. The vegan base is bananas.. literally mashed bananas- chunky.....if you want to only taste mashed bananas then go here! I got vegan base with the salty dog (caramel and pretzels) and all I could taste was the bananas which I could've made at home 😡
One of the best yogurts!  If in SF again, we will go back.

Best dessert. Ever.

This is the best Froyo I ever had!

Drop by for dessert after dinner on Polk St. There is not a lot of seating inside, but if you manage to grab a stool by the window, you may thoroughly enjoy the people watching. If you're keen to explore the flavors of rice pudding, just ask! The staff will feed you spoonfuls.

i love this place with homemade rice pudding and ice cream..so cozy and yummy!
